{"id":"ed1f83be-ccee-465e-aca6-9ab5ca614bad","title":"1495/12/12","type":"main-list-block","children":[{"id":"16c785d1-a0cf-43db-964e-91f8ec7d42a0","type":"standoff-editor-block","text":"12th December. Commissaries were sent to all the passes to watch over them.","standoffProperties":[{"id":"870ebcf1-cce5-4b21-82d4-00ab46c6f69c","type":"tei/core/date","start":0,"end":12,"value":null,"zeroPoint":false,"metadata":["0|when|1495-12-12"]},{"id":"398dfca2-902d-48fb-aa0e-b53fe59b48e0","type":"codex/time-reference","start":0,"end":12,"value":"7f3e20fa-d957-4d96-b907-057d4462aa4b","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"d6420f08-cb66-49ba-955a-36c9bf629439","type":"style/superscript","start":2,"end":3,"value":null,"zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"9f92ad59-4758-4efb-a8ce-fc9e4b06c5f8","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":15,"end":26,"value":"21f3a778-3625-4b6e-a7da-73cf157345ec","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":["0|name|Commissaries sent to watch over all the passes"]},{"id":"fe5391e8-885c-48d1-9749-7698643bba46","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":49,"end":54,"value":"5a265e95-943c-40cb-8c44-13874df0754d","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":["0|name|The passes"]},{"id":"4f05d1e2-7ccc-4122-b73f-33fc0e763dc7","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":70,"end":73,"value":"5a265e95-943c-40cb-8c44-13874df0754d","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]}],"blockProperties":[]},{"id":"310812b2-f5e1-4e09-b6a3-42ce50cf3e90","type":"standoff-editor-block","text":"","standoffProperties":[],"blockProperties":[]},{"id":"802caded-bd5d-45c8-8104-9d33855ee38a","type":"standoff-editor-block","text":"The same day the news reached us that the Tiber had risen so high at Rome that the water was up to the first story on the Banks, and was several braccia above the mark of former years. Many cattle perished, and also men, especially those who were imprisoned in the vaults of towers, and others besides.","standoffProperties":[{"id":"00d2a875-8ecd-46fe-805c-310985891c0e","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":30,"end":31,"value":"f219551f-c528-4666-8ada-4b95b7476b58","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":["0|name|The Florentines"]},{"id":"7f17edc7-9e5b-44d5-b376-0878f8524271","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":42,"end":46,"value":"4d3a6d6e-5841-4c6a-aeed-6af48d96eb76","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":["0|name|Tiber"]},{"id":"82c95a11-d030-408e-b563-782f99655e91","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":69,"end":72,"value":"501a8a32-2c8a-4934-9060-8c7e36339f0f","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":["0|name|Rome"]},{"id":"49551b4d-ec80-406e-a6c4-081a66b9593b","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":103,"end":113,"value":"9c5e9111-27a2-4720-9270-ce1ebf24b17f","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":["0|name|The first story on the Banks of the Tiber in Rome"]},{"id":"743d0144-ee4a-485e-86ba-7ec557fab231","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":122,"end":126,"value":"d6386233-c85c-4331-a436-13324dda9fc7","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":["0|name|The Banks of the Tiber in Rome"]},{"id":"dd0cd3b0-e91b-477e-a79d-454250d8e1fc","type":"style/italics","start":145,"end":151,"value":null,"zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"7bb0d7c7-05e7-4981-ae9e-33c1270217e6","type":"language","start":145,"end":151,"value":"it","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"867094f0-23a9-4414-8977-d44de0e07870","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":190,"end":195,"value":"08a6c228-6bbb-4808-8bdd-b7459d95cd6d","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":["0|name|Many cattle in Rome"]},{"id":"fab5cc4d-5e06-49f4-a460-1ac0068d3458","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":265,"end":270,"value":"5bc34d51-8c97-4746-8106-4ce38388d707","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":["0|name|The vaults of towers"]},{"id":"203d6a65-613d-44a0-b9c0-8a341a08d76c","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":275,"end":280,"value":"5948cd18-1b84-4329-a7f7-173624c234af","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":["0|name|Towers in Rome"]}],"blockProperties":[]},{"id":"2f864096-f87a-4560-984b-63a9434b6b10","type":"standoff-editor-block","text":"","standoffProperties":[],"blockProperties":[]},{"id":"ab3c09f0-6565-4683-bdeb-3706847b253d","type":"standoff-editor-block","text":"And I heard the following incredible thing, namely, that a woman had appeared to a shepherd in the Kingdom of Naples, and had said to him, \u0022Give me one of these sheep,\u0022 and when he gave it, she said: \u0022Cut it in half.\u0022 And when it was cut in half, there came out of it a quantity of serpents and vipers and scorpions and other horrible animals. And then she said to him: \u0022Close it up again, and join it well, and it will come back to life.\u0022 And when this was done, she said to him: \u0022Go and tell the Pope that there will be a great plague; that everyone must do penance and fast next Saturday, and not eat meat for three\u00A0days.\u0022","standoffProperties":[{"id":"5c65948b-e4c0-45af-b478-baf958fed829","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":4,"end":4,"value":"5d9cbd12-a35b-4b1c-9130-36c6786145b2","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":["0|name|Luca Landucci (b.1436 - d. 1516; apothecary)"]},{"id":"5ab61e06-c2d2-4fb1-9b74-db5038dc0b20","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":59,"end":63,"value":"64328e04-af23-4f8a-90df-3da8b7ed889d","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":["0|name|A woman who appeared to a shepherd in the Kingdom of Naples"]},{"id":"83a6ff9e-f1c9-49f6-a30f-4fd1db696864","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":83,"end":90,"value":"3a142e66-6214-46bc-8dbb-3b761212da45","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":["0|name|A shepherd in the Kingdom of Naples"]},{"id":"07bd1f34-5341-4e08-b9fd-5c1cae341e42","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":99,"end":115,"value":"8386260c-0061-47b8-b750-920532eb3988","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":["0|name|The Kingdom of Naples"]},{"id":"0b0e3877-e043-4fa9-a804-4433fb8714d8","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":134,"end":136,"value":"3a142e66-6214-46bc-8dbb-3b761212da45","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"b8c2d46e-68a2-449f-88dc-9702479a62a4","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":145,"end":146,"value":"64328e04-af23-4f8a-90df-3da8b7ed889d","