And when it was carried (to the ducal court), the chancellor could not open it. But as soon as the Signore Ludovico took it in his hand, it opened; and as he read it, he bent his head and stood for a moment lost in\u00A0wonder. And when the messenger asked for a reply, the Signore Ludovico said: \u0022It has been given,\u0022 and the messenger immediately disappeared. This gave rise to much talk: of plague, famine, and most of all, wars; which certainly did follow.","standoffProperties":[{"id":"7661710a-ce48-4d0d-a1ce-7a4e804f363b","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":46,"end":46,"value":"5d9cbd12-a35b-4b1c-9130-36c6786145b2","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"820cd48d-ca99-4b95-9706-a16398339f17","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":118,"end":121,"value":"87f21fc1-c980-4475-adba-3d610956f3fa","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":["0|name|The ghost of the murdered duke"]},{"id":"6a95a2d1-203b-4f06-8cc3-14ffc3c422a7","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":149,"end":153,"value":"9d055f06-6d26-42dd-9f51-7d0bec6c5496","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":["0|name|Milan (place)"]},{"id":"54244270-daf6-489a-a428-972fcfd629a9","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":211,"end":226,"value":"fa8535b0-75d2-45e8-9a1f-10bf06e1da40","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":["0|name|Ludovico Sforza"]},{"id":"89074fe5-a24d-4b06-9054-a5e65342938f","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":262,"end":272,"value":"cb5982e8-d3e3-4fa0-b284-bee35228cf9c","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":["0|name|The court of Duke Ludovico Sforza"]},{"id":"966960c3-265a-42f4-9bde-2c7cb44e2d4f","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":329,"end":344,"value":"fa8535b0-75d2-45e8-9a1f-10bf06e1da40","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"602d624f-ad31-4da1-b597-a9e8ca377b65","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":357,"end":359,"value":"fa8535b0-75d2-45e8-9a1f-10bf06e1da40","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"8c59999e-1bc1-4fab-a530-d8da68f7d2c3","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":385,"end":386,"value":"fa8535b0-75d2-45e8-9a